HEADWORD: Zapatera
<hw>Za`pa*te"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>aceituna
zapatera</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Olive trade)</fld> <def>A cured olive which
has spoiled or is on the verge of decomposition; loosely, an olive
defective because of bruises, wormholes, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
